  "time_ut": 1656410613,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0da7\u0ddd\u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Oil tokens are forged",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The people allege that the system of tokens issued by the government for the systematic distribution of fuel without queuing is not working properly in the Kurunegala District and that the applications issued for that are being photocopied and sold in the city of Kurunegala.",
        "According to government regulations, applications for token tickets are to be issued by the Divisional Secretariats and the Police, but at present the applications are being photocopied and sold at different prices.",
        "People at some petrol stations have even issued one leaflet printed on both sides to strangers in the queue, alleging that this is a ploy by the government to remove people from the queues and send them home.",
        "It also showed how the tokens given by some angry people were thrown away.",
        "The people who have been waiting in queues say that the people who received the tokens have come to Kurunegala from a long distance and cannot use the small amount of fuel they have to refuel."
      ],
